{
  "texts": [
    "Another possible reason is that various and massive software engineering data are publicly available for training advanced neural models.",
    "With the popularity of open-source software applications, developers share massive software requirements, source code, documents, bug reports, patches, test cases, online discussions, and logs and trace relationships among different artifacts.",
    "All such data make training specialized deep neural models for software engineering tasks feasible.",
    "To our knowledge, there have already been several surveys on deep learning for software engineering (e.g., Yang et al. [10], Watson et al.",
    "[24] and Niu et al. [25])."
  ]
}